  "prompt": "What is the difference between a vehicle and an automobile?",
  "response": "While the terms \"vehicle\" and \"automobile\" are often used interchangeably, there is a subtle difference:\n\n1. Vehicle:\n- A broader term that encompasses any means of transportation\n- Includes cars, trucks, motorcycles, bicycles, boats, airplanes, etc.\n- Refers to any device used for transporting people or goods\n\n2. Automobile:\n- A specific type of vehicle\n- A road vehicle powered by an engine\n- Typically designed to carry passengers\n- More precisely refers to cars with four wheels\n- Usually designed for personal transportation\n\nIn summary, all automobiles are vehicles, but not all vehicles are automobiles. \"Automobile\" is a more specific term within the broader category of \"vehicle.\"",
